import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=10)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=name_counts.index, y=name_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_age = data['age'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='age', y='height')
    plt.axvline(avg_age, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Age: {avg_age:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(avg_height, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    
    plt.title('What is the average age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
